 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search System Test Engineer NVIDIA 237 reviews Santa Clara, CA NVIDIA 237 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description We are looking to hire a  System Test Engineer.  The position requires a strong background in HW and SW to architect and develop manufacturing test solutions for system products at NVIDIA.
 NVIDIA is leading the way in groundbreaking developments in Artificial Intelligence, High-Performance Computing and Visualization. The GPU, our invention, serves as the visual cortex of modern computers and is at the heart of our products and services. Our work opens up new universes to explore, enables amazing creativity and discovery, and powers what were once science fiction inventions from artificial intelligence to autonomous cars. NVIDIA is looking for phenomenal people like you to help us accelerate the next wave of artificial intelligence.
 What you'll be doing:
 Define and implement manufacturing test solutions for Automotive and Data Center products.
 Investigate and introduce new manufacturing test technology and methodology to enhance production efficiency.
 Develop test strategy for new product features including identification, specification, design and qualification of test fixtures, test equipment and diagnostic software.
 Provide onsite CM support for builds as needed.
 Review and provide feedback for DFT in early design stages.
 Debug complex hardware and software issues during build phases.
 Build automated diag generation and validation infrastructure.
 What we need to see:
 5 + years experience with post silicon validation experience in Board or System products.
 BS Degree or equivalent experience
 Familiarity with manufacturing, chip to system.
 Python programming and bash scripting experience.
 Excellent communication skills.
 Experience designing and qualifying test fixtures/testers.
